ALL CHARACTERS, ORGANIZATIONS,
PLACES AND EVENTS ARE FICTIONAL

3
00:01:07,067 --> 00:01:10,236
DONGIL NEWS, KOOKIL NEWS,
DONGBUK DAILY, MINSUNG NEWS,

4
00:01:12,405 --> 00:01:15,492
MINSUNG NEWS, DONGIL NEWS,
KOOKIL NEWS, DONGBUK DAILY

5
00:01:17,035 --> 00:01:18,536
MINSUNG NEWS,
DONGBUK DAILY

6
00:01:20,246 --> 00:01:22,916
Finding out the truth behind the attack

7
00:01:22,999 --> 00:01:24,250
and stabilizing state affairs.

8
00:01:24,834 --> 00:01:27,128
Park Mu-jin, the Acting President,

9
00:01:27,212 --> 00:01:29,589
has two significant tasks to do.

10
00:01:29,839 --> 00:01:33,927
However, Acting President Park Mu-jin
has never been in an elected position.

11
00:01:34,010 --> 00:01:36,805
Given this unprecedented national crisis,

12
00:01:36,888 --> 00:01:39,099
many people are concerned about
whether or not he can show

13
00:01:39,182 --> 00:01:41,059
leadership in front
of administrative officers

14
00:01:41,142 --> 00:01:43,019
-and the National Assembly.
-He has a week.

15
00:01:43,436 --> 00:01:46,981
If he can run state affairs without
any problems for the next week,

16
00:01:47,565 --> 00:01:50,193
the headlines of every paper will change.

17
00:01:50,276 --> 00:01:51,569
"Acting President Park Mu-jin..."

18
00:01:51,653 --> 00:01:52,654
THE PRESIDENT PASSES AWAY

19
00:01:52,737 --> 00:01:54,697
"...Becomes a Strong Candidate."

20
00:01:56,116 --> 00:01:58,535
After that, the public will choose him

21
00:01:58,618 --> 00:01:59,953
as the next candidate.

22
00:02:04,290 --> 00:02:06,209
It seems like you chose him

23
00:02:06,459 --> 00:02:08,294
to be your next political partner.

24
00:02:09,003 --> 00:02:10,004
No, sir.

25
00:02:12,507 --> 00:02:14,342
He's a good man.

26
00:02:16,386 --> 00:02:19,806
But for me, I'm satisfied with serving
the late President Yang Jin-man.

27
00:02:22,308 --> 00:02:23,726
You also witnessed

28
00:02:24,394 --> 00:02:27,355
how the world criticized his good deeds.

29
00:02:30,525 --> 00:02:32,360
I'm going to choose the person who wins.

30
00:02:35,113 --> 00:02:36,489
That's a relief.

31
00:02:37,574 --> 00:02:38,908
President Park

32
00:02:39,909 --> 00:02:41,911
never even ran for class president

33
00:02:41,995 --> 00:02:44,205
when he was in school.

34
00:02:45,165 --> 00:02:46,124
In those days.

35
00:02:46,541 --> 00:02:48,001
Although he was a model student.

36
00:02:50,503 --> 00:02:51,838
Do you know what that implies?

37
00:02:54,632 --> 00:02:56,426
He doesn't have

38
00:02:57,385 --> 00:02:59,929
any desire for power.
He isn't suitable for politics.

39
00:03:00,513 --> 00:03:02,307
He just didn't have the opportunity.

40
00:03:03,391 --> 00:03:04,726
The opportunity to obtain power.

41
00:03:06,436 --> 00:03:08,855
Do you think he'll stay the same
even after witnessing

42
00:03:08,938 --> 00:03:10,982
the nation move on his orders?

43
00:03:11,608 --> 00:03:14,360
Have you ever seen someone let go
of their power willingly?

44
00:03:17,447 --> 00:03:18,990
Daddy!

45
00:03:27,332 --> 00:03:28,499
You did great.

46
00:03:28,583 --> 00:03:31,711
Daddy, I rode a spaceship.

47
00:03:31,794 --> 00:03:32,837
A spaceship?

48
00:03:33,630 --> 00:03:35,298
She's talking about the MRI machine.

49
00:03:39,052 --> 00:03:41,054
How were her results?
She's fine, right?

50
00:03:41,638 --> 00:03:44,182
She counted to ten.
She recognized us too.

51
00:03:44,641 --> 00:03:45,558
Isn't that enough?

52
00:03:46,184 --> 00:03:48,269
We have a doctor
at the Blue House as well.

53
00:03:48,353 --> 00:03:49,812
You don't need to worry, sir.

54
00:03:50,980 --> 00:03:52,106
Thank you.

55
00:03:53,691 --> 00:03:54,692
Let me see.

56
00:03:55,318 --> 00:03:58,529
Gosh. It must've hurt so much.

57
00:04:00,782 --> 00:04:03,409
Si-wan! I rode a spaceship.

58
00:04:05,495 --> 00:04:09,207
Si-wan. I said, I rode a spaceship.

59
00:04:09,290 --> 00:04:11,542
I'm serious.

60
00:04:13,670 --> 00:04:16,506
Si-wan, Si-jin's back.
You were worried about her.

61
00:04:17,090 --> 00:04:18,675
Aren't you hungry?

62
00:04:18,758 --> 00:04:20,301
Should I tell them to prepare your meal?

63
00:04:23,388 --> 00:04:26,641
I'm sorry. He's a teenager.

64
00:04:28,017 --> 00:04:29,936
You know how they are, right?

65
00:04:30,019 --> 00:04:33,189
Yes. I heard they're more frightening
than any dictator.

66
00:04:34,607 --> 00:04:36,651
You don't have to be sorry.

67
00:04:36,818 --> 00:04:39,487
They even say North Korea
won't dare invade

68
00:04:39,612 --> 00:04:41,281
because they're so frightening.

69
00:04:45,368 --> 00:04:46,661
I'm terribly sorry, sir.

70
00:04:47,370 --> 00:04:49,914
That joke was inappropriate
at a time like this.

71
00:04:51,541 --> 00:04:53,710
I'd like to apologize
for my son's rudeness.

72
00:05:01,259 --> 00:05:02,385
Is that true?

73
00:05:03,386 --> 00:05:05,972
Why else do you think he suddenly
got into a fistfight?

74
00:05:07,557 --> 00:05:10,101
The kids couldn't have physical education
because of the fine dust.

75
00:05:10,184 --> 00:05:12,895
One of the kids said it was
because the Minister of Environment

76
00:05:13,229 --> 00:05:14,897
wasn't doing his job properly.

77
00:05:15,732 --> 00:05:16,733
Well,

78
00:05:17,233 --> 00:05:18,860
that kid is a teenager too.

79
00:05:21,112 --> 00:05:23,114
It's hard for him, too.

80
00:05:24,282 --> 00:05:25,575
Think about it.

81
00:05:26,075 --> 00:05:28,745
He never imagined
he'd be living in the Blue House,

82
00:05:28,828 --> 00:05:30,496
which he only saw on the news.

83
00:05:30,997 --> 00:05:32,248
PRESIDENT OF KOREA, YANG JIN-MAN

84
00:05:32,332 --> 00:05:33,875
He probably doesn't know

85
00:05:34,167 --> 00:05:35,793
how he'll face his friends again.

86
00:05:39,380 --> 00:05:42,008
-What now?
-I still need to teach him manners.

87
00:05:42,633 --> 00:05:44,177
Puberty doesn't make him special.

88
00:05:50,975 --> 00:05:52,769
Si-wan, we need to talk.

89
00:05:57,357 --> 00:05:58,608
Si-Wan.

90
00:06:06,366 --> 00:06:08,409
Did you put something on that?

91
00:06:09,869 --> 00:06:11,329
A man's face is his life.

92
00:06:19,379 --> 00:06:21,381
I'm sorry. This is all because of me.

93
00:06:22,757 --> 00:06:23,966
We will have to live here

94
00:06:25,343 --> 00:06:26,719
for the time being.

95
00:06:28,471 --> 00:06:30,431
Someone once told me

96
00:06:31,641 --> 00:06:34,143
that you don't get paid every month
because you're good.

97
00:06:35,436 --> 00:06:38,898
You get paid so you can smile
while being criticized.

98
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:42,151
I get paid

99
00:06:43,611 --> 00:06:45,321
with the people's tax money.

100
00:06:47,782 --> 00:06:49,283
You don't need to worry about me.

101
00:06:50,660 --> 00:06:51,911
It's harder for you.

102
00:06:54,414 --> 00:06:56,165
That bothers me.

103
00:07:02,755 --> 00:07:05,133
So Si-wan, I hope you will...

104
00:07:08,845 --> 00:07:10,096
stay strong.

105
00:07:11,514 --> 00:07:13,182
-Dad.
-Yes?

106
00:07:16,227 --> 00:07:17,478
What's the Wi-Fi password?

107
00:07:24,652 --> 00:07:26,529
-I've tested all the dishes.
-Thank you.

108
00:07:28,406 --> 00:07:30,867
From now on, you may only eat
after the inspector tests them,

109
00:07:30,950 --> 00:07:33,619
whether it is at the Blue House
or elsewhere.

110
00:07:33,870 --> 00:07:35,580
Especially during times like this

111
00:07:35,663 --> 00:07:37,582
when there's a threat of attack,

112
00:07:37,665 --> 00:07:40,001
the inspection will be done
more meticulously.

113
00:07:41,169 --> 00:07:43,463
On that note, ma'am,

114
00:07:44,297 --> 00:07:46,799
could you consult with us
regarding your schedule?

115
00:07:46,883 --> 00:07:48,759
We need to ensure your safety.

116
00:07:48,843 --> 00:07:50,386
And since this is a sensitive time,

117
00:07:50,470 --> 00:07:52,889
we need to consider
the political side as well.

118
00:07:53,014 --> 00:07:54,432
I'm afraid

119
00:07:55,141 --> 00:07:56,559
I can't do that.

120
00:07:57,226 --> 00:07:59,604
I'm a lawyer.

121
00:07:59,687 --> 00:08:02,523
I have a duty to maintain
attorney-client confidentiality.

122
00:08:03,441 --> 00:08:05,776
For the next 60 days,

123
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:07,862
you are the First Lady.

124
00:08:11,824 --> 00:08:12,867
Hello.

125
00:08:18,831 --> 00:08:19,707
Is something wrong?

126
00:08:20,291 --> 00:08:21,792
Is this how you feel as well?

127
00:08:23,211 --> 00:08:26,422
For the past 15 years of our marriage,
I've been free.

128
00:08:27,548 --> 00:08:29,258
But she wants to tie me down now.

129
00:08:33,513 --> 00:08:35,056
Two months will fly by.

130
00:08:36,140 --> 00:08:39,143
After 60 days, we can go home.

131
00:08:40,102 --> 00:08:41,270
Nothing will change.

132
00:08:58,204 --> 00:08:59,205
Hello, sir!

133
00:09:01,082 --> 00:09:01,916
Hello.

134
00:09:17,098 --> 00:09:19,141
As you've requested,

135
00:09:19,225 --> 00:09:22,687
Ms. Jeong Su-jeong will be working
at the Presidential Secretariat.

136
00:09:23,104 --> 00:09:24,814
She will be formally assigned

137
00:09:24,897 --> 00:09:27,024
once her background check clears.

138
00:09:28,651 --> 00:09:29,777
We should go.

139
00:09:30,528 --> 00:09:34,031
Your official schedule awaits,
starting with the Chief of Staff meeting.

140
00:09:55,303 --> 00:09:59,599
DAY 59: MAINTAINING STATUS QUO
EPISODE 3

141
00:10:03,019 --> 00:10:04,395
I'm Jo Yong-gu from Saenal News.

142
00:10:04,478 --> 00:10:07,815
The attack on the National Assembly
Building. Was it North Korea?

143
00:10:08,733 --> 00:10:09,692
For now...

144
00:10:10,276 --> 00:10:13,321
I'm Min Ju-hong from KBC.
How likely is it that it was North Korea?

145
00:10:13,779 --> 00:10:14,780
PRESS SECRETARY
HONG SU-WON

146
00:10:15,364 --> 00:10:18,034
-The NIS--
-I'm Im Jae-suk from OPS.

147
00:10:18,117 --> 00:10:19,535
If it was not North Korea,

148
00:10:19,619 --> 00:10:22,997
was ISIS the terrorist organization
most likely responsible for it?

149
00:10:24,498 --> 00:10:25,374
Give me the mic.

150
00:10:27,877 --> 00:10:29,378
I'm Woo Sin-yeong from TBN.

151
00:10:29,462 --> 00:10:31,464
I heard
Japan's Maritime Self-Defense Force...

152
00:10:31,547 --> 00:10:33,549
dispatched the Aegis
to the East Sea yesterday.

153
00:10:39,138 --> 00:10:41,349
Ms. Woo, that was embargoed--

154
00:10:41,432 --> 00:10:43,309
Here's my question.

155
00:10:43,392 --> 00:10:45,978
I heard the reason
why they dispatched the Aegis was...

156
00:10:46,062 --> 00:10:50,608
because a North Korean submarine
entered our territorial waters.

157
00:11:00,117 --> 00:11:00,993
So it's true.

158
00:11:02,078 --> 00:11:03,663
So was it North Korea?

159
00:11:03,746 --> 00:11:06,332
-Is North Korea invading the South?
-Is a war imminent?

160
00:11:06,957 --> 00:11:09,543
-Why is the Blue House saying anything?
-Well...

161
00:11:11,003 --> 00:11:13,005
Why aren't you telling
the people the truth?

162
00:11:17,802 --> 00:11:19,053
We will take a short break.

163
00:11:20,262 --> 00:11:21,764
-Please answer us.
-What the hell?

164
00:11:25,601 --> 00:11:27,603
Where is he going?

165
00:11:29,230 --> 00:11:31,273
-What's all this?
-Tell me about it. What was that--

166
00:11:31,357 --> 00:11:34,985
I mean, didn't you write
the script for the briefing?

167
00:11:35,069 --> 00:11:36,445
Aren't you going to fix this?

168
00:11:38,364 --> 00:11:39,365
Me?

169
00:11:39,949 --> 00:11:41,283
I wrote it, but...

170
00:11:42,743 --> 00:11:45,162
And I'm not ready
for a situation like this.

171
00:11:45,996 --> 00:11:48,999
None of us was ready
for a situation like this.

172
00:11:49,709 --> 00:11:51,877
No one in this Blue House was.

173
00:11:51,961 --> 00:11:52,962
Well...

174
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:02,179
Sin-yeong, where are you going?

175
00:12:04,932 --> 00:12:06,350
We already have the headlines.

176
00:12:06,475 --> 00:12:08,978
"Acting President Park Mu-jin
Gets off to a Shaky Start."

177
00:12:09,311 --> 00:12:12,356
"The Incompetent Blue House Fails
as a Control Tower."

178
00:12:13,774 --> 00:12:16,277
I'll start by answering
Ms. Woo's question.

179
00:12:27,455 --> 00:12:31,500
Japan's Aegis has already
retreated from the East Sea.

180
00:12:32,752 --> 00:12:36,797
There was no provocation from North Korea,
and a war did not break out.

181
00:12:36,881 --> 00:12:39,258
Those are the facts I can confirm for now.

182
00:12:40,009 --> 00:12:42,261
Are you saying North Korea
wasn't behind the attack?

183
00:12:42,344 --> 00:12:44,180
If not, who was it?

184
00:12:45,181 --> 00:12:46,223
The NIS, DSSC,

185
00:12:47,224 --> 00:12:49,393
and our military forces

186
00:12:49,477 --> 00:12:53,230
are conducting thorough investigations
and are open to all possibilities.

187
00:12:53,314 --> 00:12:55,691
-Once there is a conclusion--
-Once there is,

188
00:12:56,817 --> 00:13:00,821
will it be made known
to the people and the press immediately?

189
00:13:05,576 --> 00:13:08,329
Ms. Woo's performance assessment
depends on her questions.

190
00:13:08,412 --> 00:13:11,123
And my performance assessment
depends on my silence.

191
00:13:11,874 --> 00:13:13,209
I hope this answers your question.

192
00:13:13,793 --> 00:13:18,005
Since the incident yesterday,
all kinds of fake news and rumors

193
00:13:18,088 --> 00:13:20,424
are spreading through social media.

194
00:13:21,175 --> 00:13:24,094
If the government doesn't share
the information transparently,

195
00:13:24,178 --> 00:13:27,473
the embers of the fake news
will never be put out.

196
00:13:27,556 --> 00:13:29,975
As long as the press does not publish
mere speculation,

197
00:13:30,059 --> 00:13:32,436
it won't spread like wildfire.

198
00:13:33,979 --> 00:13:36,482
The security of this nation
and its people are on the line.

199
00:13:36,774 --> 00:13:40,402
Your cooperation will be
very much appreciated.

200
00:13:41,612 --> 00:13:43,489
BLUE HOUSE

201
00:13:50,162 --> 00:13:51,413
Thank you. I'm...

202
00:13:53,499 --> 00:13:56,585
I'm the acting press secretary,
Kim Nam-wook.

203
00:14:02,842 --> 00:14:06,846
In total, 37 posts of agency heads
fell vacant due to the bombing.

204
00:14:06,929 --> 00:14:10,266
We will take immediate measures
so the Vice-Ministers

205
00:14:10,474 --> 00:14:11,684
can replace the Ministers.

206
00:14:12,977 --> 00:14:15,396
There may be a second attack
on key industries, railways,

207
00:14:15,479 --> 00:14:16,522
ships, and aircraft.

208
00:14:17,606 --> 00:14:21,235
Inspections at the Immigration Office
have been temporarily suspended.

209
00:14:22,027 --> 00:14:24,738
You can't ground everyone
across the board like that.

210
00:14:25,406 --> 00:14:29,410
Making overseas investors anxious
is the most amateur thing we could do.

211
00:14:30,536 --> 00:14:32,246
I'm Gu Yong-wan,
chief of economic affairs.

212
00:14:33,289 --> 00:14:35,875
Our most urgent priority
is to suspend bank transactions.

213
00:14:35,958 --> 00:14:37,918
The mass of people
trying to withdraw their funds

214
00:14:38,002 --> 00:14:39,753
has crippled the banks since morning.

215
00:14:40,045 --> 00:14:41,171
We can't do that, sir.

216
00:14:41,255 --> 00:14:43,924
If we suspend bank transactions,
countless numbers of small businesses

217
00:14:44,008 --> 00:14:46,218
will fall like dominoes in 48 hours.

218
00:14:46,302 --> 00:14:49,221
If we don't, the banks will go under.

219
00:14:49,513 --> 00:14:53,309
Then our economy will become brain-dead
before we even try CPR.

220
00:14:53,392 --> 00:14:55,769
But we must deal with
the personnel matters first.

221
00:14:55,853 --> 00:14:58,314
Security is our priority,
first and foremost.

222
00:14:58,397 --> 00:15:00,482
-This country's economy might fall apart.
-Listen--

223
00:15:07,740 --> 00:15:10,075
Everyone, please leave.

224
00:15:13,913 --> 00:15:15,998
Let's call it a day.

225
00:15:20,169 --> 00:15:21,670
It's all my fault.

226
00:15:22,463 --> 00:15:25,633
I thought the Blue House secretarial staff
could help President Park.

227
00:15:28,510 --> 00:15:29,845
I overestimated

228
00:15:31,305 --> 00:15:32,890
you people.

229
00:15:36,977 --> 00:15:39,730
These matters will be approved

230
00:15:39,813 --> 00:15:41,815
based on priority and order of importance.

231
00:15:44,777 --> 00:15:45,819
Let's go.

232
00:16:14,139 --> 00:16:16,308
"On the first day,
at the Chief of Staff meeting,

233
00:16:16,392 --> 00:16:20,145
Secretary Han yelled
at everyone in anger."

234
00:16:21,063 --> 00:16:23,565
This will be regarded as inaudible,

235
00:16:23,649 --> 00:16:24,858
so it won't stay on the record.

236
00:16:32,199 --> 00:16:33,993
It's a total mess.

237
00:16:36,370 --> 00:16:37,621
Did he hit menopause?

238
00:16:37,997 --> 00:16:41,583
There was nothing to be
so furious about. How odd.

239
00:16:42,251 --> 00:16:43,335
It's a message.

240
00:16:44,837 --> 00:16:48,298
"Though the Acting President is clueless,
don't think you can boss him around."

241
00:16:48,841 --> 00:16:50,426
"I'm behind him."

242
00:16:50,509 --> 00:16:53,804
"I'm the real owner of the Blue House."

243
00:16:53,887 --> 00:16:55,222
CHIEF OF CIVIL AFFAIRS
AN SE-YOUNG

244
00:16:55,305 --> 00:16:57,099
Come on. Secretary Han wouldn't do that.

245
00:16:57,182 --> 00:16:58,642
Why not?

246
00:17:00,185 --> 00:17:03,772
The only person who has the ability
to power through this state of emergency

247
00:17:04,773 --> 00:17:06,108
is Secretary Han.

248
00:17:09,361 --> 00:17:10,195
Ms. Min.

249
00:17:11,113 --> 00:17:13,991
Illegal wiretapping will bring
your entire family down.

250
00:17:15,951 --> 00:17:19,038
We basically had only one agenda

251
00:17:20,289 --> 00:17:21,457
at the meeting today.

252
00:17:23,959 --> 00:17:24,918
Anxiety.

253
00:17:26,462 --> 00:17:31,175
"We can't trust Park Mu-jin's leadership."

254
00:17:33,385 --> 00:17:36,221
You will visit
the scene of the tragedy this afternoon.

255
00:17:38,807 --> 00:17:40,267
The National Assembly Building?

256
00:17:40,350 --> 00:17:43,395
Because the citizens can't
trust you either, Mr. President.

