515
00:38:52,872 --> 00:38:55,708
Do you know what "bingdu" is?
The North Korean word for opium?

516
00:38:56,584 --> 00:38:59,086
A low-grade fever with chills
accompanied by vomiting.

517
00:39:01,213 --> 00:39:04,383
That piece of work
is suffering from withdrawal.

518
00:39:06,427 --> 00:39:07,720
No, Jin-ju isn't a user.

519
00:39:08,387 --> 00:39:10,431
I can guarantee it as her lawyer.

520
00:39:13,100 --> 00:39:14,226
Can you still guarantee it?

521
00:39:15,144 --> 00:39:18,606
We confiscated all this bingdu in Bogil,
where your client has her shop.

522
00:39:19,106 --> 00:39:21,484
It can't serve as evidence to prove
that she's a user.

523
00:39:22,151 --> 00:39:25,529
So what, then?
You'll continue to believe your client?

524
00:39:26,030 --> 00:39:27,406
Sure, go ahead.

525
00:39:28,949 --> 00:39:32,203
Honestly, how could you believe a commie,
of all people?

526
00:39:33,120 --> 00:39:34,163
Look!

527
00:39:40,711 --> 00:39:42,505
Oh, that's... Isn't that you?

528
00:39:44,465 --> 00:39:45,758
ACTING PRESIDENT'S WIFE

529
00:39:50,721 --> 00:39:52,681
HUMAN RIGHTS LAWYER CHOE GANG-YEON

530
00:40:05,861 --> 00:40:07,279
Does my wife have to accompany me?

531
00:40:07,863 --> 00:40:11,075
There are times when a picture
is worth a thousand words.

532
00:40:11,325 --> 00:40:14,495
Sense of responsibility, stability,
and credibility.

533
00:40:15,079 --> 00:40:17,123
Just one photo with Ms. Choe will convey

534
00:40:17,206 --> 00:40:19,625
everything the people want from you.

535
00:40:20,835 --> 00:40:21,919
Mr. President.

536
00:40:23,712 --> 00:40:24,547
Oh, yes.

537
00:40:27,508 --> 00:40:29,176
The Security Team strongly emphasized

538
00:40:29,260 --> 00:40:31,095
that you must wear this.

539
00:40:31,178 --> 00:40:32,096
Okay.

540
00:40:33,472 --> 00:40:36,892
I heard North Korean defectors
have been protesting all over the city

541
00:40:36,976 --> 00:40:39,437
since Mayor Kang sent
the Special Judicial Police

542
00:40:39,520 --> 00:40:41,105
to Mohyeon and Bogil.

543
00:40:41,439 --> 00:40:43,899
There are a lot of people on site,

544
00:40:44,442 --> 00:40:46,527
so the entire Security Team
has its guard up.

545
00:40:48,571 --> 00:40:49,572
Well...

546
00:40:50,948 --> 00:40:52,491
May I just go alone?

547
00:40:54,160 --> 00:40:57,746
Why? Is there a specific reason?

548
00:40:58,330 --> 00:41:00,791
My wife is an ordinary civilian
with her own career.

549
00:41:01,250 --> 00:41:02,418
I don't want to force her

550
00:41:02,501 --> 00:41:05,796
to stand before the public
just because she's my wife.

551
00:41:06,630 --> 00:41:07,548
And most importantly,

552
00:41:08,924 --> 00:41:10,551
she won't want to go.

553
00:41:19,852 --> 00:41:21,896
I didn't think you'd come.

554
00:41:22,897 --> 00:41:24,315
Especially dressed like that.

555
00:41:33,699 --> 00:41:34,700
You see,

556
00:41:36,035 --> 00:41:38,162
I'm not here
as the acting president's wife.

557
00:41:39,663 --> 00:41:40,664
I'm here as a lawyer.

558
00:41:43,751 --> 00:41:46,754
Revoke the Special Crime
Investigation Zone designations

559
00:41:47,338 --> 00:41:48,380
of Mohyeon and Bogil.

560
00:41:49,882 --> 00:41:52,801
Mayor Kang is oppressing
and discriminating against

561
00:41:52,885 --> 00:41:54,595
many innocent North Korean defectors

562
00:41:55,179 --> 00:41:56,472
for his political ambitions.

563
00:41:57,640 --> 00:42:00,559
And my client is one of those defectors.

564
00:42:03,187 --> 00:42:06,982
I can't have a proper meeting
with my client now

565
00:42:07,691 --> 00:42:08,984
because of where I am.

566
00:42:11,111 --> 00:42:12,196
But you...

567
00:42:13,322 --> 00:42:14,573
You can do it

568
00:42:15,199 --> 00:42:16,367
because of where you are.

569
00:42:28,170 --> 00:42:30,172
-It's the President.
-Please step aside.

570
00:42:30,256 --> 00:42:31,423
He's here.

571
00:42:59,994 --> 00:43:01,453
This way, sir.

572
00:43:10,796 --> 00:43:12,423
Agent Na, please.

573
00:43:14,466 --> 00:43:18,512
Can we please behave
more wisely and sensibly?

574
00:43:18,596 --> 00:43:20,264
The cable technician

575
00:43:20,848 --> 00:43:23,559
was our best lead on the bombing.

576
00:43:23,767 --> 00:43:25,978
He died while fleeing in order to hide

577
00:43:26,061 --> 00:43:27,438
whatever evidence he had.

578
00:43:28,230 --> 00:43:29,982
How can we not report this
to the Blue House?

579
00:43:30,065 --> 00:43:33,360
What exactly is there to report?

580
00:43:33,611 --> 00:43:35,446
We have no leads. We don't know his name.

581
00:43:35,529 --> 00:43:37,698
He was a John Doe
who wasn't even in the system.

582
00:43:37,781 --> 00:43:38,991
What would we report?

583
00:43:39,575 --> 00:43:41,660
Should we report
that he had eyes and ears?

584
00:43:45,372 --> 00:43:46,332
Na-gyeong.

585
00:43:47,625 --> 00:43:51,211
The president died and
the National Assembly Building blew up.

586
00:43:51,295 --> 00:43:53,380
Whom we point to as the bombers

587
00:43:53,464 --> 00:43:56,467
can start an international war
or a civil war.

588
00:43:56,550 --> 00:43:59,053
-Han-mo!
-Find definitive evidence.

589
00:43:59,637 --> 00:44:01,221
Then I'll definitely report it.

590
00:44:10,022 --> 00:44:11,482
KIM JUN-O

591
00:44:14,234 --> 00:44:17,279
Do we perhaps have
another lead on the bombing?

592
00:44:18,864 --> 00:44:19,698
What?

593
00:44:20,908 --> 00:44:23,202
Could someone have
known about it in advance,

594
00:44:24,286 --> 00:44:25,245
or was there a tip?

595
00:44:27,039 --> 00:44:28,457
That doesn't make any sense.

596
00:44:28,916 --> 00:44:31,418
If we had known, we would've prevented it.

597
00:44:32,753 --> 00:44:33,921
President Park is here.

598
00:44:37,675 --> 00:44:40,594
Don't go off the rails
and stir up trouble.

599
00:44:40,678 --> 00:44:43,555
I want to keep working with you
here in the field.

600
00:44:49,978 --> 00:44:51,522
Thank you for your service.

601
00:44:52,189 --> 00:44:53,315
Thank you for your service.

602
00:44:53,482 --> 00:44:55,442
I am Jeong Han-mo
of the NIS Terrorism Task Force.

603
00:44:57,986 --> 00:44:59,947
Do you have any leads on the bomber?

604
00:45:00,531 --> 00:45:02,324
I'm afraid we don't yet.

605
00:45:09,498 --> 00:45:11,959
I'm Han Na-gyeong,
an NIS Terrorism Task Force analyst.

606
00:45:13,585 --> 00:45:14,837
Thank you for your service.

607
00:45:19,007 --> 00:45:20,426
Let me introduce you to our agents.

608
00:45:20,509 --> 00:45:21,593
Sure.

609
00:45:21,969 --> 00:45:23,887
This is analyst Kim Yong-wu.

610
00:45:24,012 --> 00:45:25,097
Thank you for your service.

611
00:45:25,973 --> 00:45:27,182
We're heading out.

612
00:45:28,350 --> 00:45:29,727
This way.

613
00:45:33,480 --> 00:45:35,065
EMERGENCY RELIEF SERVICE

614
00:45:47,870 --> 00:45:48,746
This way, sir.

615
00:45:51,999 --> 00:45:52,916
Sir?

616
00:45:57,796 --> 00:45:58,630
Sir?

617
00:46:00,591 --> 00:46:01,508
What...

618
00:46:03,427 --> 00:46:06,638
Ms. Jeong, you didn't see me.

619
00:46:07,222 --> 00:46:08,682
But sir, you can't...

620
00:46:16,023 --> 00:46:17,107
I feel

621
00:46:18,025 --> 00:46:19,109
too shameless.

622
00:46:25,240 --> 00:46:26,200
We're on the move.

623
00:46:55,187 --> 00:46:56,355
President Park,

624
00:46:56,939 --> 00:46:58,148
you must show them.

625
00:47:00,567 --> 00:47:02,778
Show them that
the Blue House is standing strong.

626
00:47:03,987 --> 00:47:05,364
Show them

627
00:47:05,948 --> 00:47:08,075
that Korea is still on its feet.

628
00:47:14,164 --> 00:47:15,833
I am Acting President

629
00:47:17,125 --> 00:47:18,085
Park Mu-jin.

630
00:47:19,503 --> 00:47:21,964
First of all,
I send my deepest condolences

631
00:47:23,382 --> 00:47:25,175
to those of you

632
00:47:26,134 --> 00:47:27,803
who have lost their beloved family.

633
00:47:39,857 --> 00:47:44,111
The National Assembly Building,
which was the symbol of Korea's democracy

634
00:47:45,112 --> 00:47:46,113
until just yesterday,

635
00:47:46,864 --> 00:47:49,157
has become the site
of a great tragedy today.

636
00:47:56,290 --> 00:47:59,877
WHEN HOPE IS NO LONGER VISIBLE, HOPE

637
00:48:14,391 --> 00:48:16,935
However, this is also the place

638
00:48:18,020 --> 00:48:20,606
where the rescue squad
continues to search for survivors,

639
00:48:21,523 --> 00:48:23,650
and where policemen, firefighters,

640
00:48:24,568 --> 00:48:26,361
and volunteers devote

641
00:48:27,446 --> 00:48:28,572
their time and effort.

642
00:48:30,782 --> 00:48:33,368
It's the reason we can find hope

643
00:48:34,578 --> 00:48:36,455
even in the aftermath

644
00:48:37,039 --> 00:48:37,873
of a tragic attack.

645
00:48:38,457 --> 00:48:39,541
Over here!

646
00:48:40,667 --> 00:48:43,712
Is it true that a North Korean defector

647
00:48:44,296 --> 00:48:45,881
committed this attack?

648
00:48:46,840 --> 00:48:49,676
Do you agree with Mayor Kang's policy
of discrimination

649
00:48:50,260 --> 00:48:51,219
against defectors?

650
00:48:55,140 --> 00:48:57,100
What do you mean by that?

651
00:49:01,021 --> 00:49:01,980
FIND OUT THE TRUTH

652
00:49:02,564 --> 00:49:04,274
Please tell us what's going on!

653
00:49:05,859 --> 00:49:07,277
No, wait...

654
00:49:09,655 --> 00:49:10,656
Get down!

655
00:49:13,075 --> 00:49:15,118
What... What is going on?

656
00:49:15,202 --> 00:49:16,411
Get him on the ground!

657
00:49:22,584 --> 00:49:23,919
-We're moving out.
-Hurry!

658
00:49:24,044 --> 00:49:26,296
Hurry. Get him out of here.

659
00:49:33,053 --> 00:49:34,972
-Oh, no!
-My gosh!

660
00:49:35,555 --> 00:49:36,848
Oh, dear!

661
00:49:36,974 --> 00:49:38,934
What the hell is going on?

662
00:49:39,017 --> 00:49:40,852
What happened?

663
00:49:40,936 --> 00:49:43,605
-It's not a weapon.
-He wasn't attacking anyone.

664
00:49:43,689 --> 00:49:45,023
My goodness.

665
00:49:45,107 --> 00:49:46,108
WE ARE YOUR PEOPLE TOO!

666
00:49:46,274 --> 00:49:47,109
My dear God.

667
00:49:47,192 --> 00:49:49,736
"The Ill-Prepared Blue House
Makes People Relive the Nightmare."

668
00:49:49,820 --> 00:49:51,738
"The Unstable Acting President
Increases Anxiety."

669
00:49:51,822 --> 00:49:54,282
"Acting President Park

670
00:49:54,992 --> 00:49:57,327
Flees the Scene, A Total Catastrophe."

671
00:49:58,620 --> 00:49:59,621
Had he at least

672
00:50:00,789 --> 00:50:03,667
kept his vest on, his security detail
wouldn't have had to manhandle him

673
00:50:03,750 --> 00:50:05,252
and throw him into the car,

674
00:50:05,335 --> 00:50:07,838
and this humiliating photo wouldn't exist.

675
00:50:08,463 --> 00:50:10,340
He felt shameless
wearing a bulletproof vest

676
00:50:10,424 --> 00:50:13,385
in front of countless people
who lost their loved ones.

677
00:50:13,969 --> 00:50:15,595
He was there to send them his condolences.

678
00:50:16,179 --> 00:50:17,014
He was there

679
00:50:17,848 --> 00:50:20,267
for important political reasons.

680
00:50:20,976 --> 00:50:23,729
It was to show that Korea still has order,

681
00:50:23,812 --> 00:50:25,439
but we failed.

682
00:50:27,149 --> 00:50:28,608
Sincerity and heartfelt empathy?

683
00:50:28,692 --> 00:50:32,362
Those humane feelings should've stayed
in the calm and serene city of Sejong,

684
00:50:32,446 --> 00:50:33,530
not here in the Blue House!

685
00:50:40,579 --> 00:50:43,123
The man who caused a scene
at the bombing site is

686
00:50:43,623 --> 00:50:44,750
a North Korean defector.

687
00:50:45,834 --> 00:50:48,670
What he was trying to pull out
was a banner, not a weapon.

688
00:50:50,839 --> 00:50:52,966
He must've wanted to tell you
that his sick wife

689
00:50:53,133 --> 00:50:54,634
had been arrested by the SJP.

690
00:50:56,803 --> 00:50:58,180
I apologize for the team

691
00:50:59,222 --> 00:51:00,098
overreacting.

692
00:51:03,602 --> 00:51:04,436
If I had

693
00:51:05,604 --> 00:51:07,105
kept my vest on,

694
00:51:08,607 --> 00:51:10,817
they wouldn't have panicked.

695
00:51:13,945 --> 00:51:15,113
This isn't on you, sir.

696
00:51:16,948 --> 00:51:17,824
My team...

697
00:51:19,117 --> 00:51:21,286
failed to protect the late President.

698
00:51:23,205 --> 00:51:26,708
We just didn't want
to make the same mistake twice.

699
00:51:34,382 --> 00:51:35,967
About that defector, sir.

700
00:51:36,843 --> 00:51:39,721
I heard that his wife
is a client of the First Lady's.

701
00:51:40,639 --> 00:51:41,723
Sir.

702
00:51:46,186 --> 00:51:50,148
My client suffers from an illness
called Cushing syndrome.

703
00:51:50,732 --> 00:51:54,569
However, the officers holding her
in custody think she's an addict

704
00:51:55,320 --> 00:51:57,239
just because
she's a North Korean defector.

705
00:52:02,661 --> 00:52:04,538
The Special Crime Investigation Zones.

706
00:52:04,996 --> 00:52:06,331
How can I revoke the designations?

707
00:52:09,668 --> 00:52:11,044
This is unexpected.

708
00:52:11,545 --> 00:52:15,423
I didn't think you'd actively get involved

709
00:52:15,507 --> 00:52:16,800
in state affairs.

710
00:52:18,927 --> 00:52:21,471
I feel pathetic.

711
00:52:21,555 --> 00:52:25,183
There's no need to worry
about the photos taken at the site.

712
00:52:26,059 --> 00:52:27,894
They've agreed to take down the photos.

713
00:52:27,978 --> 00:52:29,020
What I'm ashamed of

714
00:52:30,355 --> 00:52:33,024
is that I had no idea just how terrified

715
00:52:34,651 --> 00:52:36,528
the people actually were.

716
00:52:38,780 --> 00:52:40,574
Not until

717
00:52:41,116 --> 00:52:43,243
I left the site today
as if running for my life.

718
00:52:45,162 --> 00:52:46,538
I must be

719
00:52:48,623 --> 00:52:50,542
at a safer place than I realized.

720
00:52:55,172 --> 00:52:58,341
The Special Crime Investigation Zone
and the Special Judicial Police?

721
00:52:58,925 --> 00:53:01,511
Unless Mayor Kang changes his mind,

722
00:53:04,848 --> 00:53:06,766
there's nothing we can do.

723
00:53:07,767 --> 00:53:09,769
What if I persuaded him in person?

724
00:53:09,853 --> 00:53:11,980
He won't sit down with you

725
00:53:12,856 --> 00:53:14,149
if he knows what it's about.

726
00:53:18,862 --> 00:53:20,488
Hold an inter-party meeting

727
00:53:20,906 --> 00:53:23,200
and invite him as a party representative.

728
00:53:23,491 --> 00:53:26,661
He wishes to have a more national image,

729
00:53:27,412 --> 00:53:28,747
so I'm sure he'll come.

730
00:53:30,457 --> 00:53:32,834
The Blue House must have
its own supply of fresh air.

731
00:53:34,711 --> 00:53:37,088
The fine dust level today is very high.

732
00:53:52,687 --> 00:53:53,980
Welcome.

733
00:53:54,064 --> 00:53:55,273
-Please have a seat.
-Sure.

734
00:54:03,615 --> 00:54:06,368
The majority party representative
fell victim to the tragedy,

735
00:54:06,451 --> 00:54:07,869
so I'll gladly step in anytime.

736
00:54:08,453 --> 00:54:10,288
I should offer you my help, Mr. President.

737
00:54:13,041 --> 00:54:16,628
Running a government isn't like
getting a driver's license.

738
00:54:17,712 --> 00:54:21,007
Sitting behind the wheel doesn't magically
give you the necessary skills,

739
00:54:22,092 --> 00:54:23,051
and we all know that.

740
00:54:26,054 --> 00:54:26,888
Mayor Kang.

741
00:54:28,348 --> 00:54:30,850
Would you revoke the Special Crime
Investigation Zone designations

742
00:54:31,184 --> 00:54:32,352
of Mohyeon and Bogil?

743
00:54:33,019 --> 00:54:36,648
I'd also like the SJP to stop
its unfairly targeted investigations.

744
00:54:38,400 --> 00:54:39,484
Unfairly targeted?

745
00:54:40,735 --> 00:54:41,569
In Seoul?

746
00:54:42,529 --> 00:54:45,865
We're enforcing a rightful
and legal section of the law

747
00:54:45,949 --> 00:54:49,035
to protect the people of Seoul
and their assets.

748
00:54:49,119 --> 00:54:51,538
You're maligning that
as unfairly targeted?

749
00:54:52,789 --> 00:54:53,665
An accomplice

750
00:54:54,666 --> 00:54:57,460
of the National Assembly Building Bombing
might be among them.

751
00:54:57,544 --> 00:54:59,004
Nothing has been confirmed.

752
00:54:59,087 --> 00:55:01,464
It's what
the ten million people of Seoul believe,

753
00:55:01,548 --> 00:55:02,424
and that

754
00:55:03,925 --> 00:55:05,051
is more important to me.

755
00:55:05,802 --> 00:55:07,178
Mayor Kang...

756
00:55:08,596 --> 00:55:10,265
I'm not staying for this.

757
00:55:10,807 --> 00:55:12,267
If you wish to talk about Seoul,

758
00:55:13,977 --> 00:55:15,687
come to City Hall, President Park.

759
00:55:20,984 --> 00:55:23,403
Aren't the defectors
also the people of Seoul

760
00:55:24,154 --> 00:55:25,405
whom you should protect?

761
00:55:27,365 --> 00:55:28,408
Why?

762
00:55:29,451 --> 00:55:30,994
Do they seem like innocent Koreans

763
00:55:31,077 --> 00:55:34,706
who came to the South
seeking warmth and freedom?

764
00:55:35,790 --> 00:55:37,500
The truth is they are nothing but runaways

765
00:55:37,584 --> 00:55:39,461
who couldn't adapt
to their system of state.

766
00:55:39,544 --> 00:55:40,628
They risked

767
00:55:41,379 --> 00:55:42,714
their lives

768
00:55:43,465 --> 00:55:45,175
to become citizens of Seoul.

769
00:55:46,009 --> 00:55:49,637
If we're talking about qualifications,
who do you think is more qualified?

770
00:55:50,555 --> 00:55:51,890
You and I

771
00:55:52,223 --> 00:55:54,893
didn't do anything
but be born in this country.

772
00:55:57,479 --> 00:56:00,315
I'm sure that
now that you're behind the wheel,

773
00:56:00,398 --> 00:56:02,150
you want to honk and step on the gas.

774
00:56:03,234 --> 00:56:04,235
But President Park,

775
00:56:05,904 --> 00:56:07,906
an unskilled driver

776
00:56:07,989 --> 00:56:11,910
should just hand over the wheel
to someone with more experience.

777
00:56:13,620 --> 00:56:15,872
You'll have nowhere to hide
if you crash and burn.

778
00:56:23,713 --> 00:56:26,716
Since it would be wrong to just sip tea
at an inter-party meeting,

779
00:56:27,759 --> 00:56:28,885
do you want a tip?

780
00:56:30,762 --> 00:56:33,556
There are two ways to handle Mayor Kang.

781
00:56:34,057 --> 00:56:36,810
Persuade or make him yield.

782
00:56:38,228 --> 00:56:40,063
You failed to persuade him,

783
00:56:40,605 --> 00:56:43,566
so that leaves you
with just one remaining option.

784
00:56:46,569 --> 00:56:49,197
You must be quite fond of President Park

785
00:56:49,948 --> 00:56:52,700
to give him a tip on handling Mayor Kang.

786
00:56:55,578 --> 00:56:58,706
It's up to me to protect my bunnies.

787
00:57:04,963 --> 00:57:06,464
An executive order?

788
00:57:06,631 --> 00:57:08,800
Delegate Yun Chan-gyeong suggested it?

789
00:57:09,426 --> 00:57:12,011
Yes, is it impossible?

790
00:57:12,554 --> 00:57:13,555
It's possible.

791
00:57:14,722 --> 00:57:16,724
According to the 75th Amendment
of the Constitution,

792
00:57:16,808 --> 00:57:18,393
if you order a state of emergency,

793
00:57:18,768 --> 00:57:21,813
you can dismiss
the Special Judicial Police of Seoul

794
00:57:21,896 --> 00:57:25,692
and revoke the Special Crime
Investigation Zones of Mohyeon and Bogil.

795
00:57:26,734 --> 00:57:28,111
-I'm relieved.
-Only...

796
00:57:30,530 --> 00:57:31,990
by an elected President though.

797
00:57:33,491 --> 00:57:35,201
The 71st Amendment states

798
00:57:35,285 --> 00:57:38,663
that an acting president is entrusted
with the authorities of a president,

799
00:57:38,746 --> 00:57:40,081
but only up to established orders.

800
00:57:40,165 --> 00:57:43,751
You may only give orders
to maintain the status quo.

801
00:57:44,169 --> 00:57:46,588
An executive order is a new command,

802
00:57:47,046 --> 00:57:48,715
one that disturbs the status quo.

803
00:57:50,091 --> 00:57:52,886
Are you saying
I don't have the authority then?

804
00:57:52,969 --> 00:57:56,222
The Constitution doesn't specify

805
00:57:56,639 --> 00:57:59,058
that an acting president can't issue
an executive order. But...

806
00:57:59,184 --> 00:58:02,103
Please form an advisory panel
to provide counsel.

807
00:58:02,187 --> 00:58:03,605
Yes, sir.

808
00:58:04,105 --> 00:58:08,234
It seems like you want to knock
Mayor Kang out cold, Mr. President.

809
00:58:09,152 --> 00:58:10,028
Is that a problem?

810
00:58:10,987 --> 00:58:12,238
He is currently

811
00:58:12,489 --> 00:58:15,575
the strongest presidential candidate
of the majority party.

812
00:58:15,700 --> 00:58:18,536
He shouldn't be completely
put down like this.

813
00:58:18,912 --> 00:58:20,205
It'll ruin his reputation.

814
00:58:21,080 --> 00:58:23,583
I thought you were opposed
to his policies.

815
00:58:23,666 --> 00:58:24,959
You...

816
00:58:29,714 --> 00:58:30,757
are an independent.

817
00:58:35,345 --> 00:58:37,472
Please reconsider
a political solution, sir.

818
00:58:45,271 --> 00:58:46,731
I'll go after her.

819
00:58:51,444 --> 00:58:53,530
If you insist on an executive order,

820
00:58:53,613 --> 00:58:55,657
the opposing party will say
you're abusing your power.

821
00:58:56,491 --> 00:58:58,034
They'll suggest impeachment

822
00:58:58,618 --> 00:59:01,162
and turn the presidential election around
in their favor.

823
00:59:01,871 --> 00:59:04,415
That's why Ms. Yun offered you that tip.

824
00:59:04,499 --> 00:59:09,003
She wanted to ruin Mayor Kang's reputation
and have you impeached.

825
00:59:15,802 --> 00:59:19,389
Are you only against the executive order

826
00:59:19,472 --> 00:59:21,849
because Mayor Kang
is from the majority party?

827
00:59:22,141 --> 00:59:24,269
You're taking sides.
Are you allowed to do that?

828
00:59:24,352 --> 00:59:25,770
This is the Blue House!

829
00:59:25,853 --> 00:59:28,356
What's wrong with taking sides, Ms. Jeong?

830
00:59:29,691 --> 00:59:32,151
-Because--
-To a lifer in the government like you,

831
00:59:32,235 --> 00:59:34,654
a change in regime
seems like a battle for power.

832
00:59:34,737 --> 00:59:37,407
However, to a government employee
who was specially recruited like me,

833
00:59:37,490 --> 00:59:39,659
it's the succession of certain policies.

834
00:59:45,415 --> 00:59:48,626
Decentralization of power
has been President Yang's desire.

835
00:59:51,296 --> 00:59:53,339
I agree that Mayor Kang isn't likable.

836
00:59:53,673 --> 00:59:56,926
However, when it comes to
decentralization of power,

837
00:59:57,010 --> 00:59:59,846
he is the only politician
who shares President Yang's vision.

838
01:00:01,431 --> 01:00:04,726
PROMOTING
DECENTRALIZATION OF POWER

839
01:00:04,809 --> 01:00:06,477
Since the bombing,

840
01:00:07,145 --> 01:00:11,190
I haven't been able to cry out loud
and mourn

841
01:00:11,274 --> 01:00:13,234
for my boss of 20 years.

842
01:00:13,985 --> 01:00:15,194
Because I'm apologetic,

843
01:00:16,487 --> 01:00:17,572
angry,

844
01:00:19,032 --> 01:00:20,491
and infuriated by the injustice.

845
01:00:23,536 --> 01:00:25,622
His ideas,
which were written on these pages...

846
01:00:26,956 --> 01:00:28,583
I must

847
01:00:29,959 --> 01:00:31,753
see them become a reality.

848
01:00:36,924 --> 01:00:39,719
That is my way of mourning him.

849
01:01:03,701 --> 01:01:06,245
Without the help
of the presidential staff,

850
01:01:07,497 --> 01:01:09,499
nothing will be easy,
from Cabinet meetings

851
01:01:09,582 --> 01:01:11,209
to challenging the opposing party.

852
01:01:12,794 --> 01:01:16,089
Do you still want to try
the executive order?

853
01:01:17,674 --> 01:01:19,258
There's no other way.

854
01:01:22,095 --> 01:01:23,471
Then

855
01:01:24,639 --> 01:01:26,182
please remember this.

856
01:01:27,558 --> 01:01:29,227
Once you issue the executive order

857
01:01:29,310 --> 01:01:31,396
and subdue Mayor Kang,

858
01:01:32,146 --> 01:01:34,107
you will have begun

859
01:01:34,649 --> 01:01:39,237
the Park Mu-jin administration.

860
01:01:40,363 --> 01:01:43,032
With all the prominent figures
of the majority party gone,

861
01:01:43,116 --> 01:01:46,285
people will naturally begin to look to you

862
01:01:46,369 --> 01:01:48,371
as a strong presidential candidate.

863
01:01:48,871 --> 01:01:53,418
I only wish to do what I must
in this position now.

864
01:01:53,501 --> 01:01:55,169
What you want doesn't matter.

865
01:01:56,796 --> 01:02:00,508
People will have expectations
on their own volition

866
01:02:01,217 --> 01:02:03,302
and then quickly turn their backs to you.

867
01:02:03,386 --> 01:02:07,932
The media, using verification
as a justification, will question you.

868
01:02:08,391 --> 01:02:12,103
Your political enemies will dig
into you, your family, and friends

869
01:02:12,186 --> 01:02:14,647
to find a weak spot they can exploit.

870
01:02:16,733 --> 01:02:18,025
There's a chance

871
01:02:18,735 --> 01:02:21,070
you'll never return
to the life you once had.

872
01:02:22,530 --> 01:02:23,990
The same goes for your family.

873
01:02:25,825 --> 01:02:27,201
Would you be OK with that?

874
01:02:28,911 --> 01:02:29,996
Why

875
01:02:31,497 --> 01:02:32,749
are you telling me this?

876
01:02:35,918 --> 01:02:38,713
Becoming acting president
wasn't your choice,

877
01:02:39,922 --> 01:02:41,632
but this matter is.

878
01:03:12,580 --> 01:03:13,456
Mr. President,

879
01:03:13,539 --> 01:03:16,542
I'm calling about the advisory board
regarding the executive order.

880
01:03:18,377 --> 01:03:20,254
-Sir?
-Ms. Jeong,

881
01:03:22,006 --> 01:03:24,091
could I get back to you on that?

882
01:03:47,240 --> 01:03:48,407
You're up late today.

883
01:03:51,828 --> 01:03:53,079
Is something wrong?

884
01:03:59,752 --> 01:04:01,712
My client Jin-ju...

885
01:04:05,925 --> 01:04:07,134
She died

886
01:04:08,469 --> 01:04:09,512
just now.

887
01:04:12,682 --> 01:04:15,393
All she needed was a hormone shot
to get better,

888
01:04:17,103 --> 01:04:19,146
but I wasn't able to get that for her.

889
01:04:22,108 --> 01:04:23,734
While crossing the Tumen River

890
01:04:24,902 --> 01:04:28,197
and going through Kunming
and Laos to get here,

891
01:04:30,533 --> 01:04:33,452
she survived
several near-death situations.

892
01:04:34,954 --> 01:04:37,582
That's how she got to South Korea,

893
01:04:38,583 --> 01:04:41,168
but this nation couldn't
give her a simple shot

894
01:04:42,128 --> 01:04:43,963
and caused her death.

895
01:04:46,716 --> 01:04:47,717
I wasn't

896
01:04:48,217 --> 01:04:50,177
able to do anything.

897
01:04:52,346 --> 01:04:54,265
I'm her lawyer,

898
01:04:55,182 --> 01:04:58,436
but I was worried
that people might judge me,

899
01:04:59,437 --> 01:05:00,563
and I was afraid

900
01:05:01,981 --> 01:05:04,483
it would harm you somehow.

901
01:05:10,031 --> 01:05:11,908
-Gang-yeon.
-Why...

902
01:05:14,035 --> 01:05:15,369
couldn't you do anything?

903
01:05:16,746 --> 01:05:18,080
What were you afraid of?

904
01:05:20,708 --> 01:05:24,086
We did absolutely nothing...

905
01:05:26,380 --> 01:05:28,090
even though we were in a position
to do so.

906
01:05:51,781 --> 01:05:53,449
What should we do, Secretary Han?

907
01:05:54,075 --> 01:05:56,494
We need an emergency meeting
with the police and prosecutors.

908
01:05:56,577 --> 01:05:58,079
What is it?

909
01:05:59,455 --> 01:06:02,792
North Korean defectors
are enraged by Heo Jin-ju's death

910
01:06:02,875 --> 01:06:05,920
and gathering on social media
and in various communities.

911
01:06:06,754 --> 01:06:10,174
They seem to be planning a huge memorial
at Gwanghwamun this Saturday.

912
01:06:12,301 --> 01:06:13,219
The problem is

913
01:06:13,970 --> 01:06:16,722
that another organization is scheduled
to gather there that day.

914
01:06:16,973 --> 01:06:18,099
It can't be...

915
01:06:18,224 --> 01:06:20,518
The extremists that
assaulted the defectors in Bogil

916
01:06:20,601 --> 01:06:22,520
are registered to gather there.

917
01:06:23,354 --> 01:06:26,440
We can't let that happen.
If they get into a conflict--

918
01:06:26,524 --> 01:06:28,234
Then our worst fear will come true.

919
01:06:28,317 --> 01:06:29,694
Where is President Park?

920
01:06:45,793 --> 01:06:46,794
Excuse me.

921
01:06:47,086 --> 01:06:49,088
Have you seen President Park?

922
01:06:49,171 --> 01:06:50,965
He isn't answering his phone.

923
01:06:52,383 --> 01:06:53,467
No, I haven't.

924
01:07:08,107 --> 01:07:08,983
Mr. President.

925
01:07:10,401 --> 01:07:12,319
I'm glad you're here, Ms. Jeong.

926
01:07:12,403 --> 01:07:14,488
I've looked all over for you.

927
01:07:14,572 --> 01:07:16,115
Here.

928
01:07:16,198 --> 01:07:18,409
Ambassador's basic human rights,

929
01:07:18,492 --> 01:07:19,827
active provision claim...

930
01:07:20,578 --> 01:07:22,204
What does this mean?

931
01:07:22,913 --> 01:07:23,748
Excuse me?

932
01:07:25,499 --> 01:07:28,419
I was a science major,
so social studies isn't my forte.

933
01:07:33,591 --> 01:07:36,052
Did you study the Constitution
because of...

934
01:07:36,552 --> 01:07:37,386
the executive order?

935
01:07:38,387 --> 01:07:41,849
I was a science major,
and I don't know many Chinese characters.

936
01:07:49,315 --> 01:07:51,067
THE CONSTITUTION
OF THE REPUBLIC OF KOREA

937
01:07:51,150 --> 01:07:53,736
I thought the answer
would be in the Constitution,

938
01:07:54,487 --> 01:07:55,905
but it wasn't.

939
01:07:55,988 --> 01:07:57,740
I read it over and over,
but didn't get it.

940
01:07:57,823 --> 01:08:00,618
So I've decided to go with your opinion.

941
01:08:01,911 --> 01:08:05,790
The acting president can only
maintain preexisting rules.

942
01:08:06,665 --> 01:08:09,335
That's what I intend to do.

943
01:08:11,629 --> 01:08:15,549
I see you've made a decision.

944
01:08:17,593 --> 01:08:18,677
I will issue...

945
01:08:20,346 --> 01:08:21,472
an executive order.

946
01:08:24,975 --> 01:08:28,604
The orders I have to go by
as acting president

947
01:08:28,687 --> 01:08:31,232
are those that were effective
on March 4 when my term started.

948
01:08:31,732 --> 01:08:33,109
The discrimination policy

949
01:08:33,192 --> 01:08:35,861
against North Korean defectors
began the day after.

950
01:08:38,072 --> 01:08:38,948
In other words,

951
01:08:39,573 --> 01:08:43,160
within the order I am bound by
as acting president,

952
01:08:44,578 --> 01:08:46,747
the discrimination policy didn't exist.

953
01:08:55,256 --> 01:08:56,715
I issue an executive order

954
01:08:58,008 --> 01:09:01,178
to carry out my duty
to maintain preexisting orders.

955
01:09:04,598 --> 01:09:07,351
-This is risky.
-Please reconsider.

956
01:09:07,434 --> 01:09:08,477
I'm...

957
01:09:09,854 --> 01:09:11,397
I'm against this, sir.

958
01:09:19,196 --> 01:09:21,031
I didn't think you'd disagree,
Secretary Han.

959
01:09:21,699 --> 01:09:24,368
I'm the chief presidential secretary
of the Blue House.

960
01:09:24,451 --> 01:09:28,247
You will return to your school in 60 days.

961
01:09:30,624 --> 01:09:34,545
Those of us here have to carry out
the late president's legitimacy.

962
01:09:35,337 --> 01:09:37,548
I'll make the appropriate choice to do so.

963
01:09:39,884 --> 01:09:42,928
As long as I'm against this,
no one at the Blue House

964
01:09:43,012 --> 01:09:44,638
will side with you.

965
01:09:46,307 --> 01:09:47,433
They're my people.

966
01:09:53,814 --> 01:09:55,858
If you wish to issue an executive order,

967
01:09:56,650 --> 01:09:57,943
you will have to fire me.

968
01:09:59,737 --> 01:10:01,739
Wait, Secretary Han.

969
01:10:02,698 --> 01:10:04,491
Make your choice, sir.

970
01:10:19,798 --> 01:10:20,758
Secretary Cha,

971
01:10:22,843 --> 01:10:24,094
call a Cabinet meeting.

972
01:10:29,183 --> 01:10:30,059
The agenda...

973
01:10:33,687 --> 01:10:35,272
is the issue of an executive order.

974
01:10:43,113 --> 01:10:44,031
As of now,

975
01:10:46,992 --> 01:10:48,702
Secretary Han is dismissed from his job.

976
01:10:52,373 --> 01:10:53,332
Mr. President.

977
01:10:56,210 --> 01:10:57,419
That's it...

978
01:10:59,046 --> 01:11:00,214
for today's meeting.

979
01:11:01,757 --> 01:11:03,425
THE CONSTITUTION
OF THE REPUBLIC OF KOREA

980
01:11:48,178 --> 01:11:50,347
Don't forget this moment, sir.

981
01:11:57,313 --> 01:11:59,940
This is how you use authority.

982
01:12:06,780 --> 01:12:10,576
Do you still think you don't desire
power and authority?

983
01:12:17,458 --> 01:12:19,543
Did you just say "power"?

984
01:12:24,465 --> 01:12:26,508
That has nothing to do with me.

985
01:12:43,942 --> 01:12:46,403
You should've said something to me first.

986
01:12:47,863 --> 01:12:50,282
Did you want to make a point
to the secretarial staff

987
01:12:50,491 --> 01:12:52,493
that President Park
has the greatest authority

988
01:12:52,576 --> 01:12:54,578
and to be loyal
if they want to stick around?

989
01:12:56,413 --> 01:12:58,582
You were right.

990
01:12:59,917 --> 01:13:01,835
It's not that he never wanted power,

991
01:13:02,336 --> 01:13:04,671
but he just didn't have the chance.

992
01:13:10,344 --> 01:13:11,345
Then...

993
01:13:12,679 --> 01:13:14,807
is President Park your choice

994
01:13:15,599 --> 01:13:18,811
like you chose the late President Yang
30 years ago?

995
01:13:23,816 --> 01:13:26,318
You will have to carry a heavy burden now.

996
01:13:27,111 --> 01:13:30,447
You have to take care of the Blue House
without me.

997
01:13:52,344 --> 01:13:55,472
Is it true President Park
is issuing an executive order?

998
01:13:55,556 --> 01:13:59,059
-Isn't that abuse of authority?
-Isn't that grounds for impeachment?

999
01:14:07,943 --> 01:14:10,779
Stick to one thing.
Either become competent

1000
01:14:10,863 --> 01:14:12,322
or step down.

1001
01:14:15,075 --> 01:14:16,618
Please answer.

1002
01:14:18,036 --> 01:14:19,413
Please answer!

1003
01:14:21,957 --> 01:14:23,208
Please answer.

1004
01:14:23,500 --> 01:14:24,877
-Please answer.
-Wait a minute!

1005
01:14:26,044 --> 01:14:28,672
-Excuse me.
-Wait!

1006
01:14:28,755 --> 01:14:30,340
-What's this?
-Please answer!

1007
01:14:30,466 --> 01:14:31,717
What is going on?

1008
01:14:35,095 --> 01:14:36,263
Is it over already?

1009
01:14:45,522 --> 01:14:46,648
Wait!

1010
01:14:49,318 --> 01:14:52,112
What just happened? Where did he go?

1011
01:14:52,196 --> 01:14:54,823
Aren't you going to do
the afternoon brief?

1012
01:14:56,033 --> 01:14:59,036
Why? Do I have to tell you
if I'm asking a North Korean defector

1013
01:14:59,119 --> 01:15:01,622
or a Blue House adviser?

1014
01:15:03,582 --> 01:15:07,085
This is a work directive for Kim Nam-wook,
a defector and Blue House director.

1015
01:15:09,796 --> 01:15:12,090
Are you telling me to stand
in front of the cameras

1016
01:15:12,174 --> 01:15:14,635
and become the hope and dreams
of devastated defectors?

1017
01:15:15,219 --> 01:15:17,888
Go ahead if that's what you want to do,

1018
01:15:18,555 --> 01:15:20,057
but "hope and dreams"...

1019
01:15:21,725 --> 01:15:25,646
Watch what you say about
Sejong the Great or Admiral Yi Sun-sin.

1020
01:15:28,398 --> 01:15:30,108
We don't have a press secretary,

1021
01:15:30,526 --> 01:15:31,902
and you're the best option

1022
01:15:32,945 --> 01:15:33,904
among us.

1023
01:15:35,155 --> 01:15:35,989
Right?

1024
01:15:36,490 --> 01:15:38,367
Do you need more reasons?

1025
01:15:44,498 --> 01:15:46,041
He loves compliments.

1026
01:15:46,708 --> 01:15:48,502
BLUE HOUSE

1027
01:15:56,885 --> 01:15:59,513
We will now begin the afternoon brief
of March 6.

1028
01:16:02,182 --> 01:16:03,767
Acting President Park Mu-jin...

1029
01:16:07,145 --> 01:16:09,398
First, I'd like to relay my condolences

1030
01:16:09,481 --> 01:16:11,275
for the death of Ms. Heo Jin-ju

1031
01:16:11,358 --> 01:16:15,779
during the investigation
by the Special Judicial Police in Bogil.

1032
01:16:28,500 --> 01:16:29,668
President Park...

1033
01:16:44,016 --> 01:16:47,686
President Park Mu-jin has issued
an executive order to revoke

1034
01:16:47,811 --> 01:16:49,813
the designation of Mohyeon and Bogil

1035
01:16:49,896 --> 01:16:52,774
as Special Crime Investigation Zones
on March 6.

1036
01:16:58,196 --> 01:16:59,990
SPECIAL CRIME INVESTIGATION ZONE

1037
01:17:06,663 --> 01:17:09,666
-Thank God it's over.
-I know.

1038
01:17:11,418 --> 01:17:15,422
COMMIES GO HOME!

1039
01:17:15,922 --> 01:17:18,508
GO HOME!

